Package in.ac.iitb.cfilt.jhwnl.data

Interface Summary
DictionaryElement Any class that represents an element contained in the dictionary (IndexWords, Synsets, and Exceptions) must implement this //interface.
 

Class Summary
IndexWord An IndexWord represents a line of the pos_txt file.
IndexWordSet A class to simplify the access to a set of IndexWords, each containing one part of speech of the same word.
Pointer A Pointer encodes a lexical or semantic relationship between WordNet entities.
PointerTarget A PointerTarget is the source or target of a Pointer.
PointerType Instances of this class enumerate the possible WordNet pointer types, and are used to label PointerTypes.
POS Part-Of-Speech class representing four parts of speech.
Synset A Synset, or synonym set, represents a line of a WordNet pos.data file.
Word A Word represents the lexical information related to a specific sense of an IndexWord.
